Date:  0/0/1970
Source:  Nomenclature of NZ Fish
Author:  SORENSON
Vol / Page:  45
Edition:
Quote:  <i>SNAPPER </i> (a) Scientific name: <i>Chrysophrys auratus </i>. (b) Suggested commercial name[s]: Golden Snapper (c) Other common names: Schnapper; Brim (small snapper at Nelson); Tamure. (d) Principal localities where taken: From Nelson northwards to both coasts of the North Island.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1981
Source:  Fisherman's Bible
Author:  WILSON
Vol / Page:  114
Edition:
Quote:  GOLDEN SNAPPER Not a snapper at all but a relative of the Roughy. This big-eyed, Golden (or Red) Snapper is usually taken accidentally when bottom fishing for snapper. <i>Ibid.</i>

161 A Golden Moki occurs off the East Coast of the South Island.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1982
Source:  Collins Guide
Author:  AYLING
Vol / Page:  177
Edition:  1984
Quote:   <i>GOLDEN SNAPPER Centroberyx affinis (Trachichthodes affinis)</i> (Nannygai, red snapper, koarea) ... In spite of its name the golden snapper is not related to the true snapper and is in fact more similar to the roughys. ... Schools of golden snapper often move out over open sand flats ... and are then regularly caught in bottom trawls and sold as red fish.
Notes:

